---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Navbar from '../components/Navbar.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import PageHero from '../components/PageHero.astro';
import CTA from '../components/CTA.astro';
---

<Layout title="Features — FlowTree" description="Keep worktrees, AI and terminal sessions, Git changes, and IDE access together in one native macOS workspace.">
  <Navbar />
  <main>
    <PageHero eyebrow="Features" title="The working context around every branch." description="FlowTree connects the tools you already use and keeps them organised by task." />

    <section class="section-tight">
      <div class="container card-grid">
        <article class="feature-card"><div class="feature-icon">⑂</div><h3>Worktrees for every task</h3><p>Create or import isolated workspaces for features, fixes, experiments, and reviews.</p></article>
        <article class="feature-card"><div class="feature-icon mint">›_</div><h3>Persistent sessions</h3><p>Keep multiple AI, shell, test, and log sessions attached to the work they belong to.</p></article>
        <article class="feature-card"><div class="feature-icon amber">±</div><h3>Git review</h3><p>Review, stage, commit, push, merge, rebase, stash, and resolve conflicts from the same workspace.</p></article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section section-border">
      <div class="narrow">
        <div class="split-copy">
          <p class="eyebrow">Use the right model for the job</p>
          <h2>Build, test, and challenge ideas side by side.</h2>
          <p class="lede">Profiles can launch any command-based AI tool or a normal shell. Use one model to implement, another to review its decisions, and dedicated sessions for the application and tests.</p>
          <ul class="check-list">
            <li>Multiple terminal tabs for each worktree.</li>
            <li>Sessions persist when FlowTree closes.</li>
            <li>Profiles stay provider-independent.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="narrow">
        <div class="split-copy">
          <p class="eyebrow">Understand the output</p>
          <h2>See what the agent actually changed.</h2>
          <p class="lede">Move from a terminal to a focused diff without hunting down the right repository or branch.</p>
          <ul class="check-list">
            <li>Unified and side-by-side diffs.</li>
            <li>Stage files, hunks, or selected lines.</li>
            <li>Commit, amend, push, merge, or rebase.</li>
            <li>Open the exact file in your IDE when it needs attention.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section section-border">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-heading center">
          <p class="eyebrow">Stay oriented</p>
          <h2>See every stream of work at a glance.</h2>
          <p>Group worktrees into states such as Planning, In Progress, Blocked, and Review. FlowTree supports multiple repositories without mixing their working context.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card-grid">
          <article class="card"><h3>Branches and remotes</h3><p>Create, find, fetch, pull, push, and see branches already active elsewhere.</p></article>
          <article class="card"><h3>Safe Git operations</h3><p>Preview merges and rebases, protect important branches, and handle stashes and conflicts deliberately.</p></article>
          <article class="card"><h3>Your existing tools</h3><p>Open worktrees in Finder, Xcode, Visual Studio Code, Android Studio, or IntelliJ IDEA.</p></article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="narrow">
        <div class="quote-band"><blockquote>Your code stays on your Mac.</blockquote><p>FlowTree coordinates local Git, tmux, files, and the CLI tools you choose. There is no FlowTree repository backend.</p></div>
      </div>
    </section>
    <CTA />
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>
